  • Classes in numerical.analysis used by numerical 
    Class and Description
    PolynomialSplineFunction
    This class aims to extend the concept of a function through the Function interface to polynomial spline functions along with additional instance variables and methods.
  • Classes in numerical.analysis used by numerical.analysis 
    Class and Description
    Function
    This class aims to design the data structure behind the concept of a Function as an interface simply because it only requires two methods and has no instance variables.
    LinearFunction
    This class aims to implement the Function interface methods as well as incorporate various instance variables which are akin to linear functions (such as slope and intercept) and implement additional methods such as calculating the intersection point of two LinearFunction objects.
    PolynomialFunction
    This class aims to extend the concept of a function through the Function interface to polynomial functions along with additional instance variables and methods.
    PolynomialSplineFunction
    This class aims to extend the concept of a function through the Function interface to polynomial spline functions along with additional instance variables and methods.
